It might not be the best practice to interact with SH services already in the fixture but then only tests are marked with `@pytest.mark.sh_integration`. Note that by default the fixture will get called once by every test and not just once in total. So this doesn't even reduce the number of new sessions created. Instead I propose a fixture like this:

```Python
@pytest.fixture(name="session", scope="module")
def session_fixture(config):
    return SentinelHubSession(config=config)
```

- By adding this scope the fixture will get called only once per entire module. So the same object will be passed to both tests and only 1 session will be created.
- Initializing session with config object that is obtained from `conftest.py`. This way we can propagate the same credentials throughout all tests.

