The idea of the design is that each `DecodableStreamWrapper` dispatches all attributes to wrapped file object (this is not yet implemented). With that there is no need to provide a mechanism for custom decoders, because they can just use the file directly. Imagine I want to decode an image with my custom decoder, while using the default one for the annotations:

```python
from torchvision.prototype import datasets

def custom_image_decoder(buffer: BinaryIO) -> Dict[str, Any]:
    ...

def custom_decode_sample(sample):
    sample.update(custom_image_decoder(sample.pop("image")))
    return datasets.utils.decode_sample(sample)


dataset = datasets.load(...).map(custom_decode_sample)
```

